args: Aw, man... We're completely lost.\nI thought you said that going through\nthe forest would be a shortcut, Lil' Barb.
It IS a shortcut. Whether or not you get lost\nonce we're inside ain't my responsibility.
Sheesh. Always with the jabs. Ah, well. I\nstill don't know where we actually are, but\nat least we've found our way to a village.

We should be able to ask one of the locals
which way to go, and—huh? Hey, Lil' Barb.
Is something, I don't know...off...to you
about this place?
Now that you mention it, it's weirdly quiet.\nAnd I don't see a single soul around.
I've got a bad feeling about this.\nLet's take a look around the village.
Was that a child crying?!\nWhere'd it come from?
There, look—there's a kid up in the tree!
Hey mister, please help!\nHelp my mom and dad!
Some weird people in masks came, and...\nAnd they took Mom and Dad and everyone\nelse somewhere!
People in masks?! No... It couldn't be!

No two ways about it. It's the Syndicate.
They probably made off with the people
to do another one of their creepy-ass,
good-for-nothin' experiments.
That's terrible! We have to go and help\nthem, Lil' Barb!

Did I not explicitly say to hold your damn
horses? We don't even know where they
got hauled off to. First we gotta figure out
what to do.
Hey, kid. D'you see which direction\nthey dragged the good folks away?
Um, yeah! It was...to the eastern forest!
Got it. I promise you, we'll get your loved\nones back! So just wait here and rest easy!
...Sheesh. Kid's just goootta stick his nose\ninto every little mess we come across.
See that? Syndicate goons. Looks like\nthe people they kidnapped are in there.\nWhat's our game plan?

It's the brute-force option, but I think we
should charge right in. We don't want to
give them an opportunity to make any of
the villagers into hostages.

Tch. Yeah, figured it'd be somethin' like
that. You're right, though—it'd be a huge
pain if they dragged one of the villagers
out to threaten us.
(Especially with you, kid. There's no\ntellin' how you might mess things up if\nsomeone's life is on the line...)
Gotcha. Let's get in fast and crush 'em all.
Th-that's the experimental type of\nwyrmbound soldier who escaped\nfrom the research lab!
You! Bring the mana cannon here!\nNot even a wyrmbound soldier could\nshrug off a direct hit from that!
Yo, Farren! Those mooks just dragged\nout somethin' that looks real bad!
But we're surrounded by Syndicate\nsoldiers! They can't fire it now, or they'll\nget their friends caught up in the blast.
As if they give a damn about that, idiot!
See? They don't give two nuggets about\ntheir so-called pals. And they ain't done!
My body oughta be able to take one or\ntwo shots. Once you take a hit, charge\nright in before they can recoup! Got it?
Sorry, Lil' Barb! I just can't—
HA HA HA HA! How do you like THAT?!\nEven a wyrmbound soldier is toast\nbefore the might of this baby!
Hrngh... No... It's not over. It's NOT over!
What in the hell?! That was a direct hit!\nThis kid's some kinda monster...
Your cannon is in pieces. You lose. If you\ndon't want to be hurt, then get outta here!
Hrk! For the glory...of the Syndicate...!
*huff* *huff* We managed...to take them\nall down. Let's get the villagers back...to...
We're back in the village. After you fell,\nI set the villagers free, and they carried\nyou back here.
O-oh... I see. Thanks, Lil' Barb.

You can stuff your thanks, Farren.
What the hell were you thinking?
You took that cannon blast with YOUR
half of the body.
Lemme guess: you were worried about me.
I'm sorry! I just... When I thought about\nputting you in danger for my sake, I acted\nwithout thinking...

Rgh... ＂Without thinking,＂ my scaly butt!
You might've been thinking you were
gonna protect me, but you ended up
doin' exactly the opposite!

If you had gotten smoked by that cannon,
it would've left me all alone. D'you think
I coulda scrubbed those scrubs without
you?
And there's no tellin' what woulda\nhappened to the captive villagers either.
What you ended up doing was throwin'\nour chance to win into the trash AND\nputting everyone in danger.
If you wanna go belly-up, be my guest.\nBut try puttin' yourself in the shoes of the\nfolks you get caught up in your nonsense!
I'm sorry. I just...can't stand the idea\nof watching from the sidelines.
The thought of being the only survivor\nagain on account of my inaction...
Y'know what? Fine. Do whatever you want.\nIt's got nothin' to do with me.
I told you there wouldn't be a next time.\nI'll pass on pairin' up with a guy who\nclearly doesn't trust me.
If you wanna die, knock yourself out.\nUnlike you, I'm still lookin' to stay alive.\nThere's too much I wanna do.
Peace out, guy.\nThis is where we part ways.
